news.title: Over 25,000 Supertech homebuyers staring at uncertain future
news.para: Homebuyers face further delays as NBCC started the groundwork for completing 16 housing projects, comprising 49,748 homes, in Uttar Pradesh, Uttarakhand, Haryana and Karnataka.

news.title: SC’s intervention in Amrapali case made projects viable: Attorney general
news.para: Many unsold units have now been sold with court-appointed receiver and now attorney general R Venkataramani on Thursday informing the court that 6,686 flats raising Rs 3,861 crore so far.

news.title: Dharavi: 1.4 lakh units to be resettled, 35-40% of land mass to be used
news.para: ​Only 35-40% of the land mass will be used for construction in a zone where the current population density is 2.2 lakh per sqkm (as against the average 23,000 for the rest of the city).

news.title: Chintels Paradiso RWA wants company to pay rent for families that vacated flats in Gurugram
news.para: In a letter to town planner (enforcement) Amit Madholia, RWA members said the developer has failed to comply with official directives mandating rent payments to displaced residents.

news.title: Saint-Gobain reports operating income of 5.30 billion euros in 2024
news.para: Saint-Gobain said it was expecting a 2025 operating margin above 11%, slightly above the 9-11% it was predicting in its 2021-2025 strategic plan.

news.title: Tamil Nadu CM inaugurates 1,046 flats built by TNHB
news.para: ​In addition, he inaugurated 464 quarters for government officials built at a cost of Rs 116.55 crore, remotely from the Secretariat here.

news.title: Telangana government to set up committee to resolve Emaar Properties dispute
news.para: ​Emaar Properties entered into agreements in 2001 with the then state government to invest in projects such as the construction of a convention center, hotel, golf course, villas, and other developments in Hyderabad, in the erstwhile united Andhra Pradesh, said an official release.

news.title: Kerala government to acquire Elstone Estate for Wayanad landslide victims' township
news.para: However, since the list of disaster-affected families prepared by the Wayanad District Collector does not exceed 430, only Elstone Estate will be acquired for rehabilitation in the first phase, according to an official release.

news.title: Signature Global aims to achieve zero net debt in FY26 on strong sales: Chairman
news.para: The company has reduced its net debt in the October-December quarter to Rs 740 crore, from Rs 1,020 crore at the end of the second quarter of this fiscal year.

news.title: ED conducts searches against real estate companies in Delhi-NCR
news.para: The Gurugram office of the ED raided about a dozen locations in Delhi, Noida (Uttar Pradesh), and Faridabad and Gurugram (Haryana) under the provisions of the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA).

news.title: Dublin: CRH forecasts profit growth of 6 to 12% in 2025
news.para: The Irish-based, U.S.-listed firm said it did not expect a let-up this year in those two key segments in North America, where it makes about 75% of its profit, with similar trends and some signs of residential recovery evident in Europe.

news.title: Kochi: GCDA invites EoI to develop 0.5 acre land in Marine Drive
news.para: As per the document inviting EoI, the project is part of GCDA's tourism, commercial and public infrastructure development initiatives.

news.title: UltraTech Cement's shares fall by 5% on entering wires & cables segment
news.para: The plant will be set up near Bharuch in Gujarat and is expected to be commissioned by December 2026, according to a statement from UltraTech Cement.

news.title: Goa: GCZMA to charge up to Rs 27,000 to check properties
news.para: The notification issued recently also states that such fees will be applicable to govt departments, corporations, and autonomous bodies as well.

news.title: Radisson Hotel Group expands in Rajasthan with signing of Jaipur property
news.para: “We are delighted to introduce the Radisson Collection brand to Jaipur, a city steeped in culture and known for its unmatched hospitality. This will be our fourth property in the city, which has always been a leading tourism and MICE destination.

news.title: Welspun One invests over Rs 2,000 crore across nine warehousing assets
news.para: Given the increasing scale and capital intensity of these investments, Welspun One has upsized the fund through co-investments, targeting commitments of up to Rs 1,000 crore, with robust visibility of Rs 600 crore.

news.title: Germany's PBB posts net profit of $94.19 million in 2024
news.para: The bank's net profit was at 90 million euros ($94.19 million) for 2024, down from 91 million euros a year earlier.

news.title: Over 70% of women preferred real estate as the top investment choice in 2024: Survey
news.para: Women's preference for stock market investment has declined to just 2% in H2 2024, from over 20% in H2 2022.

news.title: Rohit Sharma lease out his apartment in Mumbai for Rs 2.60 lakh per month
news.para: Rohit and his father, Gurunath Sharma bought the same apartment in March 2013 for Rs. 5.46 crore and is rented out for Rs. 2.6 lakh, reflecting a 6% rental yield, according to IGR property registration documents.

news.title: Shop buyers on par with other housing society members: Bombay HC
news.para: The divisional joint registrar had confirmed a Sept 2022 dy registrar order which directed inclusion of names of 12 shopkeepers as society members.
